{
  "texts": [
    "Diff Discrete [77] considers how to backpropagate gradients through a discrete communication channel (between 2 agents) with unknown noise.",
    "An encoder/channel/decoder system is modeled, where the encoder is used to discretize a real-valued signal into a discrete message to pass through the discrete communication channel, and the decoder is used to compute an approximation of the original signal.",
    "Later they show that the encoder/channel/decoder system is equivalent to an analog communication channel with additive noise.",
    "With the additional assumption that training is centralized, the gradient of the receiver with respect to real-value messages from the sender can be computed to allow backpropagation.",
    "DCSS [63] also considers a noisy setting."
  ]
}